<subSubSection id="77A250A2FEE48720D9A8C7F4FA647FF0" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3F070329FEE48720D9A8C7F4FB787C44" blockId="306.[136,778,173,2070]" lastBlockId="306.[810,1452,173,710]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720D9A8C7F4FED678C3" bold="true" box="[189,305,1500,1526]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720D82CC7F4FDB378C0" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1920" box="[313,596,1499,1526]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrodorsalis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720D82CC7F4FDB378C0" box="[313,596,1499,1526]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Ventrifossa nigrodorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread species, with high abundance in tropical waters of the western Pacific (
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720D85EC408FD9F7B0F" author="Merrett, N. R. &amp; Iwamoto, T." box="[331,632,1568,1594]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="723 - 781" refId="ref294511" refString="Merrett, N. R. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (2000) Pisces Gadiformes: grenadier fishes of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific Ocean. Taxonomy and distribution, with ecological notes. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 184, 723 - 781." type="journal article" year="2000">Merrett &amp; Iwamoto 2000</bibRefCitation>
; Iwamoto 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DBE0C408FF427B6E" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
2015). For further morphological information see the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720D867C44BFD927B4B" author="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Hubbs, C. L." box="[370,629,1635,1662]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="369 - 588" refId="ref286072" refString="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Hubbs, C. L. (1920) The macrouroid fishes of the Philippine Islands and the East Indies. United States National Museum Bulletin, 100 (vol. 1, pt. 7), 369 - 588. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13637" type="journal article" year="1920">Gilbert &amp; Hubbs 1920</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720DB9CC44CFECA7B95" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R." pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="473 - 570" refId="ref288733" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R. (1997) Pisces Gadiformes: taxonomy of grenadiers of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 176, 473 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; Merrett (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720D871C4AEFD797B95" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A." box="[356,670,1669,1696]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="105 - 243" refId="ref289322" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A. (1999) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) from the continental slope of western and northwestern Australia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 51, 105 - 243." type="journal article" year="1999">Iwamoto &amp; Williams (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. It has not been reported from Japanese waters, but is known from the East 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEE48720D9FCC4E1FECB7BD6" box="[233,300,1737,1763]" name="China" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">China</collectingCountry>
Sea off 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEE48720D89CC4E1FE3C7BD6" box="[393,475,1737,1763]" name="Taiwan" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720D8FFC4E1FD577BD1" author="Shao, K. - T. &amp; Ho, H. - C. &amp; Lin, P. - L. &amp; Lee, P. - F. &amp; Lee, M. - Y. &amp; Tsai, C. - Y. &amp; Liao, Y. - C. &amp; Lin, Y. - C. &amp; Chen, J. - P. &amp; Yeh, H. - M." box="[490,688,1737,1764]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="233 - 271" refId="ref299493" refString="Shao, K. - T., Ho, H. - C., Lin, P. - L., Lee, P. - F., Lee, M. - Y., Tsai, C. - Y., Liao, Y. - C., Lin, Y. - C., Chen, J. - P. &amp; Yeh, H. - M. (2008 a) A checklist of the fishes of southern Taiwan, northern South China Sea. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, (suppl. 19), 233 - 271." type="journal article" year="2008">
Shao 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DB3FC4E2FD847BD6" box="[554,611,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
2008a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720DBA9C4E1FCE27BD6" author="Shao, K. - T. &amp; Iwamoto, T. &amp; Ho, H. - C. &amp; Cheng, T. - Y. &amp; Chen, C. - Y." box="[700,773,1737,1763]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="17 - 29" refId="ref299606" refString="Shao, K. - T., Iwamoto, T., Ho, H. - C., Cheng, T. - Y. &amp; Chen, C. - Y. (2008 b) Species composition and distribution pattern of grenadiers (family [sic] Bathygadidae, Macrouridae, and Macrourididae [sic]) from Taiwan. In: Orlov, A. M. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (Eds.), Grenadiers of the World Ocean: Biology, Stock Assessment, and Fisheries. American Fisheries Society Symposium 63. American Fisheries Society, Maryland, pp. 17 - 29." type="book chapter" year="2008">2008b</bibRefCitation>
; Iwamoto 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720D9E7C4C4FECD7A30" box="[242,298,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
2015). Although Okamura (1982) reported this species from 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEE48720D85EC526FE6C7A1D" box="[331,395,1806,1832]" name="Japan" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Japan</collectingCountry>
based on two specimens collected from Tosa Bay, these specimens were subsequently allocated as 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFEE48720D835C57AFE6C7A59" box="[288,395,1874,1900]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720D8ABC57AFF247ABB" authority="Okamura, 1984" authorityName="Okamura" authorityYear="1984" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhipidodorsalis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720D8ABC57AFD6A7A59" box="[446,653,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">V. rhipidodorsalis</emphasis>
Okamura, 1984
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720D9D8C55CFDCE7ABB" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R." box="[205,553,1907,1934]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="473 - 570" refId="ref288733" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R. (1997) Pisces Gadiformes: taxonomy of grenadiers of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 176, 473 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; Merrett (1997:561)</bibRefCitation>
highlighted marked color variation between three populations within the New Caledonian region, viz., the first group from the north of 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEE48720D99DC5F2FF557AC1" box="[136,178,2010,2036]" name="Fiji" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, the second from the Chesterfield and Bellona Plateaus, and the last from off 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FEE48720D895C5D4FDD77523" box="[384,560,2044,2070]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720DBB3C5D4FBF17DFD" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R." box="[678,1046,173,2070]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="473 - 570" refId="ref288733" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R. (1997) Pisces Gadiformes: taxonomy of grenadiers of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 176, 473 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; Merrett 1997:553</bibRefCitation>
). Iwamoto 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DD8CC286FB327DF2" box="[1177,1237,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">et al.</emphasis>
(2015:115) wrote: “the existence of seemingly widely scattered populations of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720DA5AC2DAFBEF7C3E" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1920" box="[847,1032,241,267]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrodorsalis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DA5AC2DAFBEF7C3E" box="[847,1032,241,267]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">V. nigrodorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
heighten the possibility that other species lie hidden under the cloak of that species name as currently circumscribed, and they may be unveiled after closer study of more specimens”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F070329FEE48720DA4AC351FA647FF0" blockId="306.[810,1452,173,710]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DA4AC351FAEA7CA6" bold="true" box="[863,1293,377,403]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Relationships and comparisons.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720DC27C351FC5A7C80" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1920" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrodorsalis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DC27C351FC5A7C80" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Ventrifossa nigrodorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720DDB1C3B4FACA7C80" baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1188,1325,412,437]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersonii">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DDB1C3B4FACA7C80" box="[1188,1325,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">V. petersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Alcock 
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DC83C3B4FA4B7C80" box="[1430,1452,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FEE48720DA3FC395FB667CE2" author="Wood-Mason, J. &amp; Alcock, A." box="[810,1153,445,471]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" pagination="119 - 138" refId="ref302996" refString="Wood-Mason, J. &amp; Alcock, A. (1891) Natural history notes from H. M. Indian marine survey steamer ' Investigator ', commander R. F. Hoskyn, R. N., commanding. Series II., no. 1. On the results of deep-sea dredging during the season 1890 - 91. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 6, 8, 16 - 34, 119 - 138, pls. VII-VIII. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939109460385" type="journal article" year="1891">Wood-Mason &amp; Alcock, 1891</bibRefCitation>
), an Indian Ocean species also characterized by the presence of a prominent black spot on the first dorsal fin. The latter species differs most notably from 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720DAAAC00CFB8A7F08" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1920" box="[959,1133,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrodorsalis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DAAAC00CFB8A7F08" box="[959,1133,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">V. nigrodorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that an area of spinuleless scales is broadly developed posterior to the first dorsal-fin base (vs. absent or only narrowly developed). [Data for 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFEE48720DC82C040FC707F96" baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Ventrifossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersonii">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFEE48720DC82C040FC707F96" italics="true" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">V. petersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are based on 
<specimenCount id="29BEC8A0FEE48720DD30C0A1FB977F91" box="[1061,1136,649,676]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" type="generic">2 spec.</specimenCount>
collected from the Timor Sea (BKSU 16714 and BSKU 16715, 
<quantity id="F840AECCFEE48720DD8AC083FAD97FF3" box="[1183,1342,683,710]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.38" metricValueMax="3.3899999999999997" metricValueMin="3.37" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" unit="mm" value="33.8" valueMax="33.9" valueMin="33.7">33.7–33.9 mm</quantity>
HL).]
</paragraph>
